A lease agreement, in no smaller type than twelve (12) point font, shall be executed by the client and the assisted-living community and shall include but not be limited to:
Client data, for the purpose of providing service, to include:
Emergency contact person's name;
Name of responsible party or legal guardian, if applicable;
Attending physician's name;
Information regarding personal preferences and social factors; and
Advance directive under KRS 311.621 to 311.643, if desired by the client.
Assisted-living community's policy regarding termination of the lease agreement;
Terms of occupancy;
General services and fee structure;
Information regarding specific services provided, description of the living unit, and associated fees;
Provisions for modifying client services and fees;
Minimum thirty (30) day notice provision for a change in the community's fee structure;
Minimum thirty (30) day move-out notice provision for client nonpayment, subject to applicable landlord or tenant laws;
Provisions for assisting any client that has received a move-out notice to find appropriate living arrangements prior to the actual move-out date;
Refund and cancellation policies;
Description of any special programming, staffing, or training if an assisted-living community is marketed as providing special programming, staffing, or training on behalf of clients with particular needs or conditions;
Other community rights, policies, practices, and procedures;
Other client rights and responsibilities, including compliance with KRS 194A.705(2) and (3); and
Grievance policies that minimally address issues related to confidentiality of complaints and the process for resolving grievances between the client and the assisted-living community.
